This paper is about neural machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper proposes a variational model for neural machine translation, which involves probabilistic modeling and inference, and thus could also be categorized under "Machine Learning" (cs.LG) and "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI). The paper also uses neural networks as the main tool for modeling and training, which could fall under "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE) and "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV).
